$version Hand-crafted Nexys Video per-bit fixture $end
$comment 8 LED bits, 8 switch bits, 5 button bits, OLED MOSI, HDMI in/out pixel data, and audio sample stream — all as INDIVIDUAL per-bit signals (no vector buses). Tests the auto-bind service's per-bit fallback tier and exercises the LED / switch / button slots. $end
$date 2026-05-04 $end
$timescale 1ns $end
$scope module top $end
$var wire 1 ! led_0 $end
$var wire 1 " led_1 $end
$var wire 1 # led_2 $end
$var wire 1 $ led_3 $end
$var wire 1 % led_4 $end
$var wire 1 & led_5 $end
$var wire 1 ' led_6 $end
$var wire 1 ( led_7 $end
$var wire 1 ) sw_0 $end
$var wire 1 * sw_1 $end
$var wire 1 + sw_2 $end
$var wire 1 , sw_3 $end
$var wire 1 - sw_4 $end
$var wire 1 . sw_5 $end
$var wire 1 / sw_6 $end
$var wire 1 0 sw_7 $end
$var wire 1 1 btnC $end
$var wire 1 2 btnU $end
$var wire 1 3 btnL $end
$var wire 1 4 btnR $end
$var wire 1 5 btnD $end
$var wire 1 6 oled_mosi $end
$var wire 24 7 hdmi_in_data $end
$var wire 24 8 hdmi_out_data $end
$var wire 16 9 audio_left $end
$upscope $end
$enddefinitions $end
